<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-16T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-16T19:00:00-05:00" n="292" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d292">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">722.2315/2665: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Norweb</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-16T19:00:00-05:00">December 16, 1941—7
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>524. From the Under Secretary. Your 691, December 15, 6 p.m. I have
                                discussed this encouraging information with my Argentine and
                                Brazilian colleagues. I hope you will do everything possible to
                                expedite a favorable reply. Please let me know as soon as
                                possible.</p>
                            <p>In view of the information contained in your telegram under
                                reference, we have agreed to hold in abeyance the suggestions
                                formulated by the Argentine Minister for Foreign Affairs. The
                                acceptance of the 1936 line would be far more expedient from every
                                point of view. [Welles.]</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>